The paper deals with the formal language theory and logic characterization of Floyd languages, which are also known as Operator Precedence Languages. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). Additionally, the paper mentions the closure properties and local parsability of Floyd languages, which are related to Parsing and Language Processing (cs.PL). The use of monadic second-order logic (MSO) also suggests a connection to Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the inclusion of Floyd languages in various other classes, which could be related to Data Structures (cs.DS) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
